{
  "body": "The file `List.pod6` contains some relatively new verbiage which discourages the use of the `flatmap` method in favor of calling `map` followed by `flat`.  Using `flatmap` is called \"bad practice\" and \"confusing.\"  But flat-mapping is a common technique in many programming languages, and there seems to be no particular reason to avoid in in Perl 6.  Therefore, I would request that this warning be removed.\r\n",
